==English==
===Noun===
'''gas''' (''[[uncountable]] and [[countable]]'')

# (''countable'') A fundamental state of matter that is intermediate between [[liquid]] and [[plasma]].  A gas can only be contained if it is fully surrounded by a [[solid]].  A gas can [[condense]] into a liquid, or can (rarely) become a [[solid]] directly.
# (''uncountable''; ''North American'') (''short form of [[gasoline]]'') A derivative of [[petroleum]] used as [[fuel]].
# Methane or other waste gases trapped in one's belly as a result of the digestive process.  ''My tummy hurts so bad, I have '''gas'''.''

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[vapor]] / [[vapour]]
*(2): (''North American'') [[gasoline]], (''British'') [[petrol]]
*(3): (''slang'') [[fart]] (when gas is released)

